defaultI gave oral evidence to the House of Commons Health Committee hearing on Management of Long Term Conditions on 12 November 2013. During that session I offered to send the committee a note on the definition of frailty in patients.  The National Clinical Director for Integration and Frailty, John Young, has kindly drafted a note.  That note is attached.
defaultNHS England will be continuing to work to ensure that there is greater understanding of the nature and importance of frailty and ways of addressing it proactively.
