defaultThis means the person is vulnerable to dramatic, sudden changes in health triggered by seemingly small 
defaultevents
default such as a minor infection or
default a change in 
defaultmedication. A person with frailty therefore typically presents in crisis with the “classic” frailty syndromes of delirium (acute confusion); sudden immobility (stuck in a chair or in bed); or a fall (and subsequent unsafe walking). 
